com.pump.image.gif.block

Class GifBlock

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pump.image.gif.block.GifBlock
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GifConstants
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GifColorTable, GifExtensionBlock, GifGraphicRenderingBlock, GifHeaderBlock, GifImageDataBlock, GifLogicalScreenDescriptor, GifTrailerBlock

    public abstract class GifBlock
extends java.lang.Object
implements GifConstants
    A GifBlock is the most fundamental object a GIF can be broken down into.

    These blocks are all carefully detailed in the GIF file format specification, and the GifBlock's in this package [should] follow those descriptions to the letter.

      • writeSubBlocks

        protected static byte[] writeSubBlocks(byte[] data)
        Creates a large block of data as a series of GIF sub-blocks, followed by a sub-block terminator of 0x00.

        A GIF sub-block is defined as follows:
            7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0   Field Name       Type
            +---------------+
          0 |               | Block Size       Byte
            +---------------+
          1 |               |
            +-             -+
          2 |               |
            +-             -+
          3 |               |
            +-             -+
            |               | Data Values     Byte
            +-               +
        up  |               |
            +-   . . . .   -+
        to  |               |
            +-             -+
            |               |
            +-             -+
        255 |               |
             +---------------+

        Parameters:
        data - a large chunk of data
        Returns:
        a series of sub-blocks, followed by a terminator byte
